               <p>CHARLES JAMES. I am a <rs id="t18321129-224-viclabel1267" type="occupation">camp-equipage maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321129-224-victim1965 t18321129-224-viclabel1267"></join>, and live in Coventry-street. On the 30th of November, about twelve o'clock at night, I was going home, and in <placeName id="t18321129-224-crimeloc1268">King-street, Covent-garden</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18321129-224-crimeloc1268" type="placeName" value="King-street, Covent-garden"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18321129-224-crimeloc1268" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321129-224-off1265 t18321129-224-crimeloc1268"></join>, I missed from my pocket a pocketbook, containing a bill for 15l.; I was close to the houses - a person tried to pass between me and the houses; there was not room, and during that time I felt a motion at my pocket - I looked round, and saw a person walking away from me; I put my hand to my pocket, and my book was gone - I went after the person, and the Policeman laid hold of him; it was the prisoner - I saw him drop the book while the Policeman held his collar.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321129-224-person1966">
                  JOHN 
                  JOHNSON
               <interp inst="t18321129-224-person1966" type="surname" value="JOHNSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-224-person1966" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-224-person1966" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Policeman. I took the prisoner, as Mr. James said he had taken his pocket-book; both my hands were engaged - I looked down, and saw the pocket-book slip down at his feet; he seemed surprised that he should be apprehended; there were two youngsters there, who ran off, but I could not follow them.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had been to Chelsea, looking for employ, and then went to see my mother - I met two young men, and had a glass or two with them, and in King-street I was charged with this.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18321129-224-verdict1269" type="verdictDescription">
